✅ PORTFOLIO WEBSITE IMPROVEMENT PROMPT

Prompt:

I have a personal portfolio website for a junior frontend developer.
Please redesign and improve it professionally with the following requirements:

1. Homepage Hero Section

Add a strong headline:
“Hi, I’m Adeoye Timothy — a Junior Frontend Developer”

Add a subtitle:
“I build responsive, user-friendly web applications using React and JavaScript.”

Include two call-to-action buttons:

View Projects (scrolls to Projects section)

Download CV (links to my CV PDF)

Make the hero section modern, clean, and responsive.

2. About Section

Replace the existing content with:

I am a Junior Frontend Developer and engineering student at Lagos State University (LASU). I enjoy building clean, responsive, and interactive web applications using modern frontend technologies. I am passionate about learning, improving my skills, and contributing to real-world projects.

3. Projects Section

For each project, display:

Project title

Short description

Technologies used

Live demo button

GitHub repository button

Example project content:
Food Recipe App
A dynamic recipe web application that fetches real-time data from a public API, allowing users to explore and filter meals.

4. Contact Section

Include:

Email

LinkedIn

GitHub

Remove WhatsApp contact option

Keep the design professional and recruiter-friendly

General Requirements

Use clean UI/UX

Fully responsive (mobile, tablet, desktop)

Modern frontend best practices

Professional look suitable for internships, SIWES, and junior frontend roles

✅ HOW TO USE THIS PROMPT

You can:

Paste it into ChatGPT and ask for:

React code

Tailwind CSS version

Plain HTML/CSS/JS version

Give it to a developer

Use it while rebuilding your portfolio yourself
